Emilia "Emilie" Maria Sara Sofia Uggla (24 February 1819 in Karlstad – 15 February 1855 in Upperud), was a Swedish noble classical concert pianist and concert singer.
She made her debut in 1830, when she participated anonymously in a public concert in  Stockholm at the age of eleven.
In 1831, she held a public concert under her own name at Stora Börssalen in Stockholm.
1831–43, she toured Sweden, Norway and Denmark, and in 1838–40 in Finland and Russia, where she performed at the Imperial court of the Czar.
